    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         angus-activation — CVE-2025-7962
         VERDICT: FALSE POSITIVE

         OWASP incorrectly matches this CVE against angus-activation via CPE
         cpe:2.3:a:eclipse:angus_mail because both projects share the
         org.eclipse.angus namespace.

         CVE-2025-7962 is an SMTP injection vulnerability in angus-mail (Jakarta
         Mail SMTP implementation). angus-activation is a completely separate
         project — it implements Jakarta Activation (MIME type handling) and
         contains no SMTP code whatsoever.

         References:
           https://github.com/dependency-check/DependencyCheck/issues/8130
           https://github.com/dependency-check/DependencyCheck/issues/8144
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>
            FALSE POSITIVE: CVE-2025-7962 is an SMTP injection vulnerability in
            angus-mail, not angus-activation. OWASP incorrectly matches via shared
            CPE namespace (eclipse:angus_mail). angus-activation implements Jakarta
            Activation (MIME types) and contains no SMTP code.
            See: https://github.com/dependency-check/DependencyCheck/issues/8130
        </notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/org\.eclipse\.angus/angus\-activation@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2025-7962</cve>
    </suppress>

