    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         io.netty:* (any module) — CVE-2026-42582
         VERDICT: FALSE POSITIVE (wrong module + already-fixed version)

         CVE-2026-42582 affects netty-codec-http3, a module this project does
         not depend on (no HTTP/3 usage — this is a Kafka/Spring Boot backend).

         OWASP maps every io.netty:* artifact to the same broad CPE
         cpe:2.3:a:netty:netty:<version>, with no module-level distinction.
         CVE-2026-42582's NVD configuration matches this broad CPE regardless
         of version — netty-transport, netty-transport-native-unix-common, and
         netty-codec each in turn were flagged at 4.1.135.Final, even though
         4.1.135.Final is past the 4.1.133.Final release that fixed this CVE
         upstream.

         Narrower regexes were tried (netty-transport@.*, then
         netty-transport.*@.*) but this is whack-a-mole: Netty has dozens of
         modules and any can surface after the next NVD refresh. Widened to the
         full io.netty groupId — this project doesn't use netty-codec-http3
         regardless of which sibling module NVD maps the CVE onto next.

         Tracked upstream: dependency-check/DependencyCheck#8576 (Netty CVEs
         mismatched across sibling modules via the shared broad CPE).
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>
            FALSE POSITIVE: CVE-2026-42582 affects netty-codec-http3, which this
            project does not use (no HTTP/3). OWASP maps every io.netty:* artifact
            to the same broad cpe:2.3:a:netty:netty:* CPE. netty-transport,
            netty-transport-native-unix-common, and netty-codec each appeared in
            turn at 4.1.135.Final (past the 4.1.133.Final fix). Suppression widened
            to full io.netty groupId to stop the whack-a-mole.
            Tracked upstream: dependency-check/DependencyCheck#8576
        </notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/io\.netty/.*@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-42582</cve>
    </suppress>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         swagger-ui (embedded in springdoc-openapi) — DOMPurify CVEs
         CVE-2026-41238, CVE-2026-41239, CVE-2026-41240, GHSA-39q2-94rc-95cp
         VERDICT: AWAITING FIX IN SPRINGDOC-OPENAPI

         These CVEs affect DOMPurify 3.3.2 bundled inside swagger-ui-5.32.2.jar
         which ships with springdoc-openapi 2.8.17 (current latest). The fix
         exists in DOMPurify 3.4.0 and has been available since April 2026, but
         springdoc-openapi has not yet released a version bundling it.

         DOMPurify is a client-side JavaScript XSS sanitizer used by the
         Swagger UI HTML/JS bundle. None of the CVEs affect Java server-side
         code. Swagger UI in this project is:
           - Accessible only in development/staging (not production)
           - Protected by JWT authentication on all API endpoints
           - Not exposed to untrusted HTML input from end-users

         CVE-2026-41238 (CVSS 6.9): prototype pollution XSS bypass — requires
           a prior prototype pollution gadget in the same browser context.
         CVE-2026-41239 (CVSS 6.8): SAFE_FOR_TEMPLATES bypass in RETURN_DOM mode.
         CVE-2026-41240 (CVSS 6.0): FORBID_TAGS/FORBID_ATTR inconsistency.
         GHSA-39q2-94rc-95cp (CVSS 5.3): ADD_TAGS short-circuit bypass.

         All CVSS scores < 7.0 — do not block the build, but suppressed here
         to keep the report clean and document the tracking status.

         Renovate will open a PR when springdoc-openapi releases a version
         bundling DOMPurify >= 3.4.0. Re-evaluate by 2026-12-31.
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>
            AWAITING FIX: DOMPurify 3.4.0 fixes all four CVEs but springdoc-openapi
            2.8.17 (current latest) still bundles swagger-ui with DOMPurify 3.3.2.
            All CVEs are client-side JS only (CVSS 5.3-6.9, non-blocking). Swagger
            UI is JWT-protected and not exposed to untrusted HTML input in this
            project. Renovate will PR when springdoc-openapi ships DOMPurify 3.4.0+.
        </notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:javascript/DOMPurify@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-41238</cve>
    </suppress>
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>See DOMPurify suppression note for CVE-2026-41238.</notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:javascript/DOMPurify@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-41239</cve>
    </suppress>
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>See DOMPurify suppression note for CVE-2026-41238.</notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:javascript/DOMPurify@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-41240</cve>
    </suppress>
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>See DOMPurify suppression note for CVE-2026-41238.</notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:javascript/DOMPurify@.*$</packageUrl>
        <ghsaId>GHSA-39q2-94rc-95cp</ghsaId>
    </suppress>

